experiment PCBVEL
instrument ESR
start 2012 12 07 1800
end 2012 12 07 2400
status R
description PCB location and associated horizontal plasma flows in the nightside
contact Timo Pitkänen
email timo.pitkanen@oulu.fi
operator Antti Kero
submitter Antti Kero
resources FI(18)
notes
We need simultaneously the mainland VHF (tau8) and UHF (bella) at low
elevation (30 deg) to the north (UHF az = 342 deg) and the ESR radar (taro)
at low elevation (30 deg) to the south (az = 151 deg) to get estimates of the
PCB location and associated horizontal plasma flows in the nightside
ionosphere.
